# Overview

**CompuTec ProcessForce** extends the standard **Material Requirements Planning** (**MRP**) functionality in **SAP Business One** by adding advanced production planning and **Manufacturing Order** creation capabilities.

The solution integrates directly with the **SAP Business One MRP Wizard** and **Order Recommendation** window, allowing planners to continue using familiar SAP processes while benefiting from **CompuTec ProcessForce** manufacturing features.

:::warning[important]

If you experience slow performance when opening the **MRP Wizard** with **CompuTec ProcessForce** enabled, consider enabling **Direct Data Access** mode. This can significantly improve performance in databases with a large number of **Item Master Data** records. [Read more](../../administrator-guide/licensing/license-server/configure-computec-service-manager.md).
:::

## How It Works

**CompuTec ProcessForce** works alongside the standard **SAP Business One MRP** process:

- The **MRP Wizard** runs using standard **SAP Business One** functionality.
- MRP recommendations are generated by **SAP Business One**.
- The **Order Recommendation** window allows users to create **CompuTec ProcessForce Manufacturing Orders** directly from the generated recommendations.
- **Manufacturing Orders** are automatically scheduled using backward scheduling, ensuring production is planned to meet the required due date.

### Creating Manufacturing Orders from MRP Recommendations

To create **Manufacturing Orders** from **MRP** recommendations:

1. Run the **MRP Wizard** in **SAP Business One**.

    ![MRP Wizard](./media/overview/mrp-wizard.png)

2. Complete the MRP process and select **Save Recommendations**.
3. Open the **Order Recommendation** window from the context menu.
4. Select the recommendations for which you want to create **Manufacturing Orders**.

    ![Order Recommendation](./media/overview/order-recommendation.png)

5. Click **Update**.
6. Confirm the operation when prompted.

7. After the process is completed:

    - A confirmation message displays the number of **Manufacturing Orders** created.
        ![System Message](./media/overview/system-message.png)

    - A summary report lists all documents generated from the selected recommendations.
        ![Created Recommendations](./media/overview/created-recommendations.png)

### Result

For each recommendation converted into a **Manufacturing Order**:

- A **CompuTec ProcessForce Manufacturing Order** is created.
- The **Manufacturing Order** status is set to ``Scheduled``.
- The order is scheduled using ``backward`` scheduling based on the required completion date.
- Production dates are automatically calculated to help ensure the finished goods are available when needed.

![Manufacturing Order](./media/overview/manufacturing-order.png)
